A Jos Upper Area Court in Kasuwan Nama, Jos, Plateau State, has dissolved the nine-year old marriage between Sadiya Adamu and her husband, Ifeanyi Nnadili, over the former’s ill-tempered nature. Delivering judgment, the judge, Suleiman Lawal, granted Ifeanyi his prayer of divorce and ordered both parties to go their separate ways. According to the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN), Ifeanyi in his petition told the court that he could no longer cope with and tolerate his wife’s temper. “She is angry and hostile towards me. We fight all the time,” he said. YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE We Have Not Had Water Supply In Months ― Abeokuta Residents In spite of the huge investment in the water sector by the government and international organisations, water scarcity has grown to become a perennial nightmare for residents of Abeokuta, the Ogun State capital. This report x-rays the lives and experiences of residents in getting clean, potable and affordable water amidst the surge of COVID-19 cases in the state…Provost of Federal College  Provost of Federal College Selfies, video calls and Chinese documentaries: The things you’ll meet onboard Lagos-Ibadan train The Lagos-Ibadan railway was inaugurated recently for a full paid operation by the Nigerian Railway Corporation after about a year of free test-run. Our reporter joined the train to and fro Lagos from Ibadan and tells his experience in this report…Provost of Federal College  Provost of Federal College ORITAMEFA BAPTIST MODEL SCHOOLS, (OBMS), IBADAN 
